## Introduction to strings 
s='coffee'
t='bread'
print(s)                                 coffee
print(t)                                 bread
print(s+t)                               coffeebread
# let us discussed when we print s plus t it will be concatenate, that is 
probly new word for all
# What will happen if i were simply say s of 0,even this we discussed, it will show the first letter of s, s of first letter of s, if I were to say s of 2 and so on.
print(s[0])                             c
print(s[1])                             0
# What will happen if you s of 1 here and then 3 here it does something else, it is starting from the first number and  does not goes up to 3, it goes 1 less, so s of 1 and s of 2 is (of).It is called String slicing.
print(s[1:3])                           of
print(s{1:5])                           offe 
print(s[3:5])                           fe
print(s+t)                              coffebread #concatenate two
print(s-t)                              error #nothing to do
s='0123456789'
